# idea2lunch.com — Cursor Rules

## Stack
- Next.js 15 App Router, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS
- Vercel (project: mamapromptangel, team: eddiebms-projects)
- Upstash Redis (orders, sessions, stats)
- Stripe + Paystack (dual-processor — Paystack for African countries)
- Resend (email + magic-link auth)
- OpenRouter → Gemini 2.5 Flash (brief gen, taglines, support agent)
- OpenAI gpt-image-1 (logo starter)
- Recraft API (logo pro, SVG vector)
- Hetzner server 5.78.183.141 (AGE worker, cron agents)

## Code rules
- Every route must export `export const runtime = 'edge'` unless it uses Node.js-only libs
- Use `@upstash/redis` not raw fetch for Redis
- All Stripe calls use apiVersion: '2024-06-20'
- African countries list already defined in app/api/order/route.ts — import it, don't redefine
- Redis key conventions:
  - `order:{sessionId}` — full order object
  - `customer:{email}:order` — index by email
  - `auth:token:{token}` — magic-link token (15min TTL)
  - `pro:{email}` — Pro editor subscriber flag
  - `edits:{email}:{weekISO}` — free-tier edit counter
  - `stats:deploys` — running deploy counter
  - `leads:{YYYY-MM-DD}` — daily lead gen log
  - `brandrefresh:{email}` — brand refresh subscriber
- deployToVercel() helper already exists in app/api/webhook/route.ts — import don't rewrite
- slugify() helper already exists in app/api/webhook/route.ts — import don't rewrite
- notifyCustomer() helper already exists in app/api/webhook/route.ts — import don't rewrite

## Env vars (all set in Vercel production)
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY | STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET | STRIPE_LAUNCH_PRICE_ID
STRIPE_DESIGN_PRICE_ID | STRIPE_FULL_PRICE_ID
PAYSTACK_SECRET_KEY | UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL | UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN
RESEND_API_KEY | OPENAI_API_KEY | OPENROUTER_API_KEY
VERCEL_DEPLOY_TOKEN | NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=https://idea2lunch.com

## Env vars to add (do not use until added)
RECRAFT_API_KEY | STRIPE_PRO_EDITOR_PRICE_ID | STRIPE_BRAND_REFRESH_PRICE_ID
STRIPE_WHITE_LABEL_PRICE_ID | STRIPE_TAGLINE_PRICE_ID
STRIPE_LOGO_STARTER_PRICE_ID | STRIPE_LOGO_PRO_PRICE_ID
STRIPE_BRAND_KIT_PRICE_ID | STRIPE_REDESIGN_PRICE_ID
STRIPE_EDIT_PRICE_ID | STRIPE_SEO_PRICE_ID

## Never do
- Never stage or commit .vercel/ output artifacts
- Never re-implement deployToVercel, slugify, notifyCustomer — they exist
- Never hardcode prices — always use env var Price IDs
- Never bypass Stripe signature verification in webhooks
- Never store raw card data — Stripe/Paystack handle all PII
- Never use `any` unless casting Stripe/Paystack API responses

## Deploy command
cd ~/Documents/lunch2idea && git push && npx vercel --prod
